---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn more about Jacky Huynh and his journey through engineering, business operations, and leadership."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>

    <h1>
      Engineering Graduate, Business Builder, and Problem Solver
    </h1>

    <p class="intro">
      I'm a Mechanical Engineering graduate from Temple University who enjoys
      solving problems, building systems, and turning ideas into reality. My
      experiences range from engineering design projects and technical analysis
      to leading business operations and managing teams.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>My Journey</h2>

    <p>
      I earned my Bachelor of Science in Mechanical Engineering from Temple
      University, where I developed a foundation in design, analysis,
      manufacturing, and problem-solving through coursework, laboratory
      experience, and multidisciplinary projects.
    </p>

    <p>
      After graduation, an opportunity arose to build a business from the
      ground up. What began as a personal goal evolved into a multi-year
      experience managing projects, leading teams, developing systems, and
      navigating the challenges of operating a growing business.
    </p>

    <p>
      Although my career path temporarily moved away from traditional
      engineering roles, the experience strengthened many of the same skills
      that make successful engineers effective: problem-solving, project
      management, communication, process improvement, and continuous learning.
    </p>

    <p>
      Today, I'm combining those experiences as I return to the engineering
      field, bringing both technical knowledge and real-world leadership
      experience to the next chapter of my career.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>What I've Learned</h2>

    <p>
      Engineering taught me how to analyze problems. Business taught me how to
      execute solutions.
    </p>

    <p>
      Together, these experiences shaped the way I approach challenges today.
      Whether I'm designing a component, managing a project, improving a
      process, or leading a team, I focus on understanding the problem,
      identifying constraints, and developing practical solutions.
    </p>

    <p>
      One of the most valuable lessons I've learned is that successful projects
      require more than technical expertise. Communication, accountability,
      planning, and continuous improvement are often just as important as the
      technical solution itself.
    </p>

    <p>
      These experiences also changed how I view the world around me. Whether
      it's a machine, structure, product, or process, I naturally think about
      why it was designed a certain way, what constraints influenced those
      decisions, and how it could potentially be improved.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>What I Bring</h2>

    <div class="skills-grid">
      <div class="skill-card">
        <h3>Engineering</h3>

        <p>
          CAD Design<br />
          Engineering Analysis<br />
          Simulation<br />
          Testing & Validation<br />
          Technical Problem-Solving
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="skill-card">
        <h3>Operations</h3>

        <p>
          Project Management<br />
          Process Improvement<br />
          Documentation<br />
          Planning & Coordination<br />
          Systems Development
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="skill-card">
        <h3>Leadership</h3>

        <p>
          Team Development<br />
          Communication<br />
          Accountability<br />
          Training & Onboarding<br />
          Cross-Functional Collaboration
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>Current Focus</h2>

    <p>
      I'm seeking opportunities where I can apply both my engineering
      education and operational experience to contribute to meaningful
      projects, continue developing technically, and grow as an engineer.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="facts">
    <div class="fact-card">
      <h3>Education</h3>
      <p>B.S. Mechanical Engineering</p>
      <p>Temple University</p>
    </div>

    <div class="fact-card">
      <h3>Experience</h3>
      <p>Engineering • Operations • Leadership</p>
    </div>

    <div class="fact-card">
      <h3>Focus Areas</h3>
      <p>Design • Manufacturing • Process Improvement</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    max-width: 48rem;
    margin-bottom: 5rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .intro {
    max-width: 42rem;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  .content-section {
    max-width: 48rem;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .skills-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .skill-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 1.75rem;
  }

  .skill-card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .skill-card p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .facts {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 5rem;
  }

  .fact-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .fact-card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .fact-card p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .skills-grid,
    .facts {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>